  "prompt": "Do people see questions that are marked as needing improvement?",
  "response": "If you're talking about questions on platforms like Stack Exchange or other Q&A sites, questions that are marked as needing improvement are typically still visible to the public, but they might be flagged to indicate that they don\u2019t meet the site's quality standards. This flagging serves as feedback to the original poster to improve the question\u2019s clarity, provide more detail, or adhere to community guidelines. On some platforms, questions might be temporarily hidden or closed until they are improved. \n\nIn educational or internal platforms, the visibility of questions marked for improvement may vary based on the platform's settings or the organization's policies. In some cases, only the person who asked the question and moderators may see such flags, while in others, the entire community may see them. If you\u2019re asking about a specific platform, I could provide more detailed information if I had the name of that platform.",
